One of the men apparently offered the official R3,000 to provide official checks and authorise his brother s passport.Instead the officer alerted the Pretoria Serious Corruption Unit of the Hawks and an operation was mounted.The flight from OR Tambo was slightly delayed so the Hawks were just in time to pounce. A 36-old-man was found in possession of a fraudulent passport.A search of his luggage revealed ivory polished diamonds 10kg of wet abalone a bag of dry abalone and a bag of Lenovate ointment which is used for serious skin conditions Lupus Psoriasis and other disorders and requires a doctor s prescription.The value of his loot is estimated at R6-million.